    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - CHASSIS FEATURES - SUSPENSION DUMP
        - DIAGNOSTICS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DIAGNOSTICS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Problems in the suspension dump circuits can be can be attributed to short circuits, open circuits, a
                failed relay or a failed ECU.
            </para>
            <para>The ESC will log diagnostic trouble codes (DTCs) for problems in the
                <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290015.xml" xrefid="x08290015">switch pack</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="x08290015"/>. The ESC will also log DTCs for problems in the
                <hotlnk document="s08290_X08290187.xml" xrefid="x08290187">4-pack remote air solenoid module (RASM)
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="x08290187"/>.
            </para>
            <para>Switch pack configuration and RASM configuration and programming will vary from vehicle to vehicle.
            </para>
            <para>An electronic service tool, running the "Diamond Logic Builder&#8482;" diagnostic software, can be
                used to activate the suspension dump circuits and monitor activation of the suspension dump switch. See
                the diagnostic software manual for details on using the software.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Suspension Dump Preliminary Check</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Insure there is air pressure to the air solenoid pack, there are no air line restrictions to
                        the air powered feature, and the air powered feature is mechanically sound before performing the
                        Preliminary Check.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
